1. A statistically significant reduction in ocular itching was observed for BBOS 1.5% treatment.
2. The reduction in ocular itching for BBOS 1.5% treatment was compared to placebo.
3. The reduction in ocular itching was observed at all time points.
4. The P value for the reduction in ocular itching was less than 0.0001.
5. Measures for onset and 8-hour persistence of action reached clinical significance.
6. The clinical significance was defined as a 1.0 unit difference or more.
7. The onset and 8-hour persistence of action reached clinical significance at a majority of time points.
